147
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:07,297
Sis.

148
00:10:07,321 --> 00:10:08,336
What about mine?

149
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:09,360
Hold on, don't rush.

150
00:10:11,880 --> 00:10:14,200
A specially made
thousand-year-old ginseng.

151
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:17,216
Sis, you spent so much.

152
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:19,160
This one's even better.

153
00:10:20,640 --> 00:10:22,520
Fresh deer whip.

154
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:24,576
Eat this,

155
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:26,680
and you'll boost your fertility.

156
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:30,080
Thanks a lot.

157
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:31,480
Take these to every room.

158
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:35,016
Married a wife who can't bear kids.

159
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:36,496
Even magic pills are useless.

160
00:10:36,520 --> 00:10:37,616
All she knows is draining our energy.

161
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:38,640
Mom.

162
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:40,416
You can't just say that.

163
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:42,016
That hen that doesn't lay eggs

164
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:43,496
is still a chicken, isn't it?

165
00:10:43,520 --> 00:10:45,976
We can still keep it for the meat.

166
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,616
Or make some soup with it.

167
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:50,056
A disobedient hen needs to be tamed.

168
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:52,920
I came this time to help you
teach it properly.

169
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:55,960
Hmph, just wait and see
how I deal with you.

170
00:10:57,280 --> 00:11:00,440
Let's see what tricks you can pull now.

171
00:11:12,560 --> 00:11:13,497
Auntie.

172
00:11:13,521 --> 00:11:15,696
My kite got stuck in a tree.

173
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:17,720
Can you help me get it down?

174
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:36,336
Mom said you took a lot of money
from our family.

175
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:37,616
She said you're a very bad person.

176
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:39,216
Once you're gone,

177
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:41,360
we can get our money back.

178
00:11:52,630 --> 00:11:59,730
♪ Even one second of truth is enough
to lose myself in it ♪

179
00:12:00,470 --> 00:12:06,466
♪ Whether you're light or a lie,
I can't pull myself away ♪

180
00:12:06,490 --> 00:12:12,930
♪ In this game,
truth or lie no longer matters ♪

181
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:15,000
What are you doing?

182
00:12:17,360 --> 00:12:18,360
You're hurt.

183
00:12:18,960 --> 00:12:20,160
The wound needs to be treated.

184
00:12:28,840 --> 00:12:29,320
No need.

185
00:12:29,760 --> 00:12:31,240
- I'll handle it myself.
- Don't move.

186
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:32,760
What is his intention?

187
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:04,400
This was my failure.

188
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:08,800
I'll keep a closer eye on you
from now on.

189
00:13:18,760 --> 00:13:20,736
I did save you once.

190
00:13:20,760 --> 00:13:21,800
A glass of wine in return.

191
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:24,440
That's not too much, right?

192
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:28,000
But I remember Inspector Huo said
it was his own fault.

193
00:13:28,760 --> 00:13:29,816
Besides, we're not at the point

194
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:31,720
where we can toast together, are we?

195
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:35,200
If I want,

196
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:39,240
we can be any kind of relationship.

197
00:13:39,880 --> 00:13:41,960
He seems to be
deliberately getting closer to me,

198
00:13:42,480 --> 00:13:44,720
trying to dig out something from me.

199
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:51,856
What are you talking about?

200
00:13:51,880 --> 00:13:53,016
Come on, dinner's ready.

201
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:54,040
Let's go eat.

202
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:57,360
Inspector Huo.

203
00:13:57,760 --> 00:13:59,056
Join us for dinner.

204
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:00,080
Sure.

205
00:14:06,040 --> 00:14:06,457
Come on.

206
00:14:06,481 --> 00:14:07,856
Let's all

207
00:14:07,880 --> 00:14:08,880
have a toast.

208
00:14:15,240 --> 00:14:16,736
Don't get too proud just yet.

209
00:14:16,760 --> 00:14:18,696
Soon you'll be burned half-paralyzed.

210
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:19,776
If not dead, then disabled.

211
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:20,576
Dad.

212
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:21,320
What kind of drink is this?

213
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:22,440
It's so strong.

214
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:24,960
I had it shipped from France.

215
00:14:25,160 --> 00:14:25,536
It's a bit strong.

216
00:14:25,560 --> 00:14:26,376
Yeah, it's kinda strong.

217
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:27,056
But it's good stuff.

218
00:14:27,080 --> 00:14:27,697
Take it easy though.

219
00:14:27,721 --> 00:14:29,016
Then... I

220
00:14:29,040 --> 00:14:30,040
I'll have some more.

221
00:14:30,480 --> 00:14:31,656
You're really playful.

222
00:14:31,680 --> 00:14:33,056
Dad, don't drink too much.

223
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:35,400
Alright, let's eat first.

224
00:15:03,580 --> 00:15:06,720
♪ Mist coils around the sleeping forest ♪

225
00:15:07,190 --> 00:15:10,370
♪ Memories scattered
through cracks of darkness ♪

226
00:15:10,740 --> 00:15:14,220
♪ How to escape this real-feeling dream ♪

227
00:15:17,770 --> 00:15:21,020
♪ Lies reflect in water's gleam ♪

228
00:15:21,250 --> 00:15:24,590
♪ Traces of existence
can never be erased ♪

229
00:15:24,870 --> 00:15:28,150
♪ How to find the self I can't reclaim ♪

230
00:15:30,470 --> 00:15:37,540
♪ Fly away, hear she says ♪

231
00:15:37,620 --> 00:15:41,566
♪ She'll fly out from
thorns of woven lies ♪

232
00:15:41,590 --> 00:15:45,166
♪ Pierce the fog,
shatter this dream tonight ♪

233
00:15:45,190 --> 00:15:48,126
♪ Burn like fire ♪

234
00:15:48,150 --> 00:15:51,570
♪ Just burn like fire ♪

235
00:15:51,780 --> 00:15:55,660
♪ The maze in the abyss starts to clear ♪

236
00:15:55,710 --> 00:15:58,396
♪ Yet night keep on whispering ♪

237
00:15:58,420 --> 00:16:01,560
♪ Surrender to fate,
no clear direction ahead ♪

238
00:16:01,840 --> 00:16:05,340
♪ She will rise as the dawn
that breaks the darkness ♪

239
00:16:05,420 --> 00:16:11,880
♪ Never slowing down,
for tomorrow cannot be stopped ♪

240
00:16:12,530 --> 00:16:15,846
♪ Surrender to love and find the way ♪

241
00:16:15,870 --> 00:16:19,390
♪ Even if fate tries to forget her ♪

242
00:16:19,620 --> 00:16:26,140
♪ Never despair,
for the heart burns with endless light ♪

243
00:16:26,550 --> 00:16:28,410
♪ Waiting for dawn ♪

